    </metadata>
    <styling>
      <style xml:id="basic" tts:textAlign="center" />
    </styling>
  </head>

  <body>
    <div style="basic">
        <p begin="00:00:00.840" end="00:00:08.760" tts:direction="ltr">Hello, visitors. This is an example of a
<br />stellar exploratory story.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:09.080" end="00:00:13.720" tts:direction="ltr">Let's dive in to our beginning of the
<br />story.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:13.720" end="00:00:20.790" tts:direction="ltr">Pops. This is an example that I'm using,</p>
        <p begin="00:00:20.790" end="00:00:24.310" tts:direction="ltr">and it is related to the help desk.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:24.310" end="00:00:26.650" tts:direction="ltr">Many companies have help desks,</p>
        <p begin="00:00:26.650" end="00:00:30.530" tts:direction="ltr">and they are looking to resource their
<br />allocations.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:30.530" end="00:00:35.410" tts:direction="ltr">So I'm going to go ahead and begin my
<br />story.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:35.410" end="00:00:39.610" tts:direction="ltr">Hello, I'm Lean, and I'm here to update
<br />you on</p>
        <p begin="00:00:39.610" end="00:00:44.500" tts:direction="ltr">where our employees need the most help
<br />from the help desk,</p>
        <p begin="00:00:44.500" end="00:00:47.500" tts:direction="ltr">specifically so that we can use</p>
        <p begin="00:00:47.500" end="00:00:51.920" tts:direction="ltr">their time resources in the most effective
<br />manner.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:51.920" end="00:00:54.160" tts:direction="ltr">Let's start with the big picture.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:54.160" end="00:00:58.340" tts:direction="ltr">The help desk is overwhelmed from
<br />department issues,</p>
        <p begin="00:00:58.340" end="00:01:00.980" tts:direction="ltr">and they are unable to tackle</p>
        <p begin="00:01:00.980" end="00:01:04.340" tts:direction="ltr">the recent infrastructure and security
<br />requests</p>
        <p begin="00:01:04.340" end="00:01:07.220" tts:direction="ltr">that are coming from management.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:07.220" end="00:01:09.840" tts:direction="ltr">Now, that is a problem as</p>
        <p begin="00:01:09.840" end="00:01:14.280" tts:direction="ltr">clearly security is something top of mind
<br />and a priority,</p>
        <p begin="00:01:14.280" end="00:01:17.950" tts:direction="ltr">and so let's dive into what is happening.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:17.950" end="00:01:23.680" tts:direction="ltr">I've created a dashboard here to identify
<br />some of the pain points</p>
        <p begin="00:01:23.680" end="00:01:29.440" tts:direction="ltr">that I think might be helpful for you to
<br />understand some of the issues.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:29.440" end="00:01:32.280" tts:direction="ltr">Now, you can bring it up on your own so
<br />that you</p>
        <p begin="00:01:32.280" end="00:01:35.300" tts:direction="ltr">can dive more deeply into this.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:35.300" end="00:01:39.120" tts:direction="ltr">I'm going to take you through this
<br />dashboard right now.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:39.240" end="00:01:42.440" tts:direction="ltr">To highlight a few of its features.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:42.440" end="00:01:48.060" tts:direction="ltr">This is a weekly analysis for the year of
<br />2020,</p>
        <p begin="00:01:48.060" end="00:01:53.480" tts:direction="ltr">you can see here that we start on March 2
<br />and go all</p>
        <p begin="00:01:53.480" end="00:01:59.020" tts:direction="ltr">the way until October 19 to look at the
<br />time frame.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:59.020" end="00:02:00.840" tts:direction="ltr">Now, you'll notice that there are</p>
        <p begin="00:02:00.840" end="00:02:05.300" tts:direction="ltr">some key performance indicators indicated
<br />here</p>
        <p begin="00:02:05.300" end="00:02:09.950" tts:direction="ltr">at the top of the dashboard and those will
<br />relate to the highlighted bar.</p>
        <p begin="00:02:09.950" end="00:02:12.930" tts:direction="ltr">For instance, on the March 2,</p>
        <p begin="00:02:12.930" end="00:02:16.810" tts:direction="ltr">you'll see that there were 134 tickets
<br />that were issued by</p>
        <p begin="00:02:16.810" end="00:02:21.270" tts:direction="ltr">the Help Desk with a decrease of the
<br />overall average,</p>
        <p begin="00:02:21.270" end="00:02:23.390" tts:direction="ltr">so it's just using a calculation to</p>
        <p begin="00:02:23.390" end="00:02:27.530" tts:direction="ltr">determine how this week is in relation to
<br />the other weeks.</p>
        <p begin="00:02:27.530" end="00:02:33.470" tts:direction="ltr">The average days that are open is 19 for
<br />this particular period of time,</p>
        <p begin="00:02:33.470" end="00:02:37.530" tts:direction="ltr">and that is up 2.78 of the average.</p>
        <p begin="00:02:37.530" end="00:02:40.250" tts:direction="ltr">There are 15% resolved tickets,</p>
        <p begin="00:02:40.250" end="00:02:42.950" tts:direction="ltr">and you can see again how that's in
<br />relation to</p>
        <p begin="00:02:42.950" end="00:02:47.585" tts:direction="ltr">the average and where we stand in terms of
<br />satisfaction.</p>
        <p begin="00:02:47.585" end="00:02:51.000" tts:direction="ltr">Here on the right hand, you can see that</p>
        <p begin="00:02:51.000" end="00:02:54.840" tts:direction="ltr">we have broken this into four categories
<br />of severity,</p>
        <p begin="00:02:54.840" end="00:02:59.380" tts:direction="ltr">issue category, ticket status, and
<br />satisfaction breakdown.</p>
        <p begin="00:02:59.380" end="00:03:03.100" tts:direction="ltr">With this darker blue being something of</p>
        <p begin="00:03:03.100" end="00:03:08.260" tts:direction="ltr">the unassigned category and the purple
<br />being low,</p>
        <p begin="00:03:08.260" end="00:03:10.465" tts:direction="ltr">medium, and then high.</p>
        <p begin="00:03:10.465" end="00:03:13.630" tts:direction="ltr">On the issue category,</p>
        <p begin="00:03:13.630" end="00:03:21.250" tts:direction="ltr">we are denoting the colors to be
<br />specifically with 35% being access in
<br />login,</p>
        <p begin="00:03:21.250" end="00:03:25.290" tts:direction="ltr">29% on systems, and 31% on hardware.</p>
        <p begin="00:03:25.290" end="00:03:28.090" tts:direction="ltr">Then you can see that we have several
<br />tickets that are still</p>
        <p begin="00:03:28.090" end="00:03:33.180" tts:direction="ltr">open with satisfaction breakdown with a
<br />lot of unknowns.</p>
        <p begin="00:03:33.180" end="00:03:36.410" tts:direction="ltr">Also see here at the bottom of the
<br />dashboard that</p>
        <p begin="00:03:36.410" end="00:03:41.090" tts:direction="ltr">the tickets are broken down by day of the
<br />week so that we can</p>
        <p begin="00:03:41.090" end="00:03:44.330" tts:direction="ltr">begin to track when calls are coming in</p>
        <p begin="00:03:44.330" end="00:03:49.730" tts:direction="ltr">and when we need to make sure we have
<br />resources to have those calls.</p>
        <p begin="00:03:49.730" end="00:03:51.930" tts:direction="ltr">Now, in addition to all of this,</p>
        <p begin="00:03:51.930" end="00:03:59.310" tts:direction="ltr">you can go to this widget and break down
<br />according to our various departments,</p>
        <p begin="00:03:59.310" end="00:04:03.700" tts:direction="ltr">including architecture, and hardware and
<br />networking,</p>
        <p begin="00:04:03.700" end="00:04:05.940" tts:direction="ltr">security governance and software.</p>
        <p begin="00:04:05.940" end="00:04:10.280" tts:direction="ltr">This gives you the ability to really drill
<br />down to figure out if</p>
        <p begin="00:04:10.280" end="00:04:12.160" tts:direction="ltr">there are certain departments that are</p>
        <p begin="00:04:12.160" end="00:04:14.980" tts:direction="ltr">just using the help desk more frequently.</p>
        <p begin="00:04:14.980" end="00:04:19.000" tts:direction="ltr">You can also go through issue or request.</p>
        <p begin="00:04:19.000" end="00:04:23.300" tts:direction="ltr">An issue is some problem that needs to be
<br />resolved,</p>
        <p begin="00:04:23.300" end="00:04:26.540" tts:direction="ltr">whereas a request could be an upgrade of
<br />some software</p>
        <p begin="00:04:26.540" end="00:04:31.195" tts:direction="ltr">or some hardware or something that doesn't
<br />need immediate attention.</p>
        <p begin="00:04:31.195" end="00:04:36.470" tts:direction="ltr">We also have the number of days open where
<br />we have all tickets,</p>
        <p begin="00:04:36.470" end="00:04:39.370" tts:direction="ltr">and then we have increments of five,</p>
        <p begin="00:04:39.370" end="00:04:42.490" tts:direction="ltr">and this is important because we are
<br />trying to shoot</p>
        <p begin="00:04:42.490" end="00:04:46.810" tts:direction="ltr">for no tickets open more than 15 days.</p>
        <p begin="00:04:46.810" end="00:04:49.850" tts:direction="ltr">We have some internal targets that we're
<br />trying to hit.</p>
        <p begin="00:04:49.850" end="00:04:53.010" tts:direction="ltr">I can close that down or I can open that
<br />again.</p>
        <p begin="00:04:53.010" end="00:04:55.770" tts:direction="ltr">Remember, I can just switch to all</p>
        <p begin="00:04:55.770" end="00:05:00.315" tts:direction="ltr">and it creates the ability to customize
<br />the view.</p>
        <p begin="00:05:00.315" end="00:05:02.620" tts:direction="ltr">The final thing that I wanted to point out
<br />on</p>
        <p begin="00:05:02.620" end="00:05:06.340" tts:direction="ltr">the dashboard is there is the variance to
<br />selected weeks,</p>
        <p begin="00:05:06.340" end="00:05:08.520" tts:direction="ltr">where we can begin to see, for instance,</p>
        <p begin="00:05:08.520" end="00:05:10.320" tts:direction="ltr">on this March 2,</p>
        <p begin="00:05:10.320" end="00:05:13.820" tts:direction="ltr">that there was an increase by 12%.</p>
        <p begin="00:05:13.820" end="00:05:18.920" tts:direction="ltr">That's that difference between right here
<br />in relation to this March 2,</p>
        <p begin="00:05:18.920" end="00:05:20.820" tts:direction="ltr">there was an increase of 2%,</p>
        <p begin="00:05:20.820" end="00:05:23.360" tts:direction="ltr">et cetera, there was a decrease of 13%.</p>
        <p begin="00:05:23.360" end="00:05:26.500" tts:direction="ltr">If we want to select a key week,</p>
        <p begin="00:05:26.500" end="00:05:34.015" tts:direction="ltr">we can begin to also see what variances
<br />there were before and after that week.</p>
        <p begin="00:05:34.015" end="00:05:37.190" tts:direction="ltr">A lot of information to see,</p>
        <p begin="00:05:37.190" end="00:05:41.710" tts:direction="ltr">but I believe this will help you uncover
<br />some of the questions that you have,</p>
        <p begin="00:05:41.710" end="00:05:44.850" tts:direction="ltr">and you might be able to drill down even
<br />deeper into</p>
        <p begin="00:05:44.850" end="00:05:49.650" tts:direction="ltr">those questions as you begin and continue
<br />to explore this dashboard.</p>
        <p begin="00:05:49.650" end="00:05:53.750" tts:direction="ltr">However, I did want to provide some
<br />recommendations in</p>
        <p begin="00:05:53.750" end="00:06:01.150" tts:direction="ltr">this presentation to help us achieve our
<br />goals of helping the help desk.</p>
        <p begin="00:06:01.150" end="00:06:04.560" tts:direction="ltr">After my analysis of the dashboard,</p>
        <p begin="00:06:04.560" end="00:06:10.110" tts:direction="ltr">I'm recommending to redeploy the help desk
<br />to more severe cases.</p>
        <p begin="00:06:10.110" end="00:06:12.450" tts:direction="ltr">Specifically, we want to educate</p>
        <p begin="00:06:12.450" end="00:06:16.150" tts:direction="ltr">employees to troubleshoot the access and
<br />log in issues,</p>
        <p begin="00:06:16.150" end="00:06:21.730" tts:direction="ltr">which seem to be a very common issue for
<br />the Help help desk,</p>
        <p begin="00:06:21.730" end="00:06:24.730" tts:direction="ltr">but one that our employees could
<br />troubleshoot.</p>
        <p begin="00:06:24.730" end="00:06:28.320" tts:direction="ltr">The recommendations include onboarding</p>
        <p begin="00:06:28.320" end="00:06:32.220" tts:direction="ltr">training that are focused on these common
<br />access log in issues.</p>
        <p begin="00:06:32.220" end="00:06:34.040" tts:direction="ltr">The time that they are hired,</p>
        <p begin="00:06:34.040" end="00:06:39.460" tts:direction="ltr">let's get them already inculturated on how
<br />to alleviate those problems.</p>
        <p begin="00:06:39.460" end="00:06:42.140" tts:direction="ltr">There could be weekly tips in our company</p>
        <p begin="00:06:42.140" end="00:06:46.100" tts:direction="ltr">slack channel that focuses on the access
<br />or log in issues of the week,</p>
        <p begin="00:06:46.100" end="00:06:48.060" tts:direction="ltr">some things that we are seeing are hearing</p>
        <p begin="00:06:48.060" end="00:06:50.440" tts:direction="ltr">from the various employees and
<br />departments.</p>
        <p begin="00:06:50.440" end="00:06:53.360" tts:direction="ltr">Then also creating some how to videos
<br />located</p>
        <p begin="00:06:53.360" end="00:06:56.220" tts:direction="ltr">on the internal site that are quick and
<br />easy,</p>
        <p begin="00:06:56.220" end="00:06:58.860" tts:direction="ltr">and we know that individuals</p>
        <p begin="00:06:58.860" end="00:07:01.680" tts:direction="ltr">that our company love just to watch those
<br />simple videos.</p>
        <p begin="00:07:01.680" end="00:07:05.560" tts:direction="ltr">We could bring some of our culture and
<br />humor into those videos to really</p>
        <p begin="00:07:05.560" end="00:07:08.320" tts:direction="ltr">help alleviate any stress that might</p>
        <p begin="00:07:08.320" end="00:07:11.640" tts:direction="ltr">come about when it comes to these access
<br />and log in issues.</p>
        <p begin="00:07:11.640" end="00:07:16.660" tts:direction="ltr">Of course, I would love to hear your ideas
<br />that we can include here,</p>
        <p begin="00:07:16.660" end="00:07:22.055" tts:direction="ltr">and we're really hoping to discuss and
<br />determine our approach.</p>
        <p begin="00:07:22.055" end="00:07:25.270" tts:direction="ltr">Now, hopefully you have seen</p>
        <p begin="00:07:25.270" end="00:07:30.730" tts:direction="ltr">how that an exploratory story has a very
<br />messy middle.</p>
        <p begin="00:07:30.730" end="00:07:35.230" tts:direction="ltr">Clearly, there's no direct action except
<br />for what I'm proposing.</p>
        <p begin="00:07:35.230" end="00:07:37.690" tts:direction="ltr">The stakeholder or the audience could</p>
        <p begin="00:07:37.690" end="00:07:41.690" tts:direction="ltr">discover some other issue that they want
<br />to focus on,</p>
        <p begin="00:07:41.690" end="00:07:46.630" tts:direction="ltr">and that is the messy middle of a
<br />dashboard.</p>
        <p begin="00:07:46.630" end="00:07:48.130" tts:direction="ltr">However, as an employee,</p>
        <p begin="00:07:48.130" end="00:07:50.650" tts:direction="ltr">you still want to provide some insight,</p>
        <p begin="00:07:50.650" end="00:07:52.910" tts:direction="ltr">something that has lifted to the top for
<br />you,</p>
        <p begin="00:07:52.910" end="00:07:57.490" tts:direction="ltr">but then expect there to be a time delay
<br />or maybe a redirect</p>
        <p begin="00:07:57.490" end="00:08:02.410" tts:direction="ltr">or pivot according to what your
<br />stakeholder finds most valuable.</p>
        <p begin="00:08:02.410" end="00:08:09.550" tts:direction="ltr">You can still do a leaf behind that can
<br />help direct the conversation.</p>
        <p begin="00:08:09.550" end="00:08:13.800" tts:direction="ltr">Here we've got the one that summarizes
<br />what</p>
        <p begin="00:08:13.800" end="00:08:18.220" tts:direction="ltr">the presentation was to redeploy the help
<br />desk to more severe cases or</p>
        <p begin="00:08:18.220" end="00:08:21.800" tts:direction="ltr">those other infrastructure or security
<br />issues that management</p>
        <p begin="00:08:21.800" end="00:08:25.460" tts:direction="ltr">is requesting that we're showing that that
<br />access and</p>
        <p begin="00:08:25.460" end="00:08:29.600" tts:direction="ltr">login does monopolize about 35% of</p>
        <p begin="00:08:29.600" end="00:08:34.865" tts:direction="ltr">the help desk resources and providing some
<br />of those recommendations.</p>
        <p begin="00:08:34.865" end="00:08:38.490" tts:direction="ltr">So, hopefully you are feeling and</p>
        <p begin="00:08:38.490" end="00:08:40.230" tts:direction="ltr">understanding the difference between</p>
        <p begin="00:08:40.230" end="00:08:42.810" tts:direction="ltr">exploratory and explanatory and
<br />dashboards.</p>
        <p begin="00:08:42.810" end="00:08:45.450" tts:direction="ltr">They really have very different metals,</p>
        <p begin="00:08:45.450" end="00:08:49.370" tts:direction="ltr">and you need to make sure that you're
<br />assessing what your purpose is,</p>
        <p begin="00:08:49.370" end="00:08:53.770" tts:direction="ltr">who your audience is, what your data is
<br />telling you and showing,</p>
        <p begin="00:08:53.770" end="00:08:57.750" tts:direction="ltr">and when's the appropriate time to do
<br />either.</p>
        <p begin="00:08:57.750" end="00:09:00.010" tts:direction="ltr">I hope that this has been helpful,</p>
        <p begin="00:09:00.010" end="00:09:05.230" tts:direction="ltr">and I can't wait to learn more about the
<br />stories that you will create.</p>
    </div>
  </body>
</tt>
